@NODE "Main" "Main"

@{JCENTER}@{B}MiraMP3 GUI V1.1a@{UB}
© 1998-1999 Massimo Perfini
Freeware

@{JLEFT}Welcome to MiraMP3 GUI, the first graphic interface which enables you to use all the current MPEG audio encoders for the Amiga.
Since no Amiga MPEG encoder has a GUI, I decided to create one for ALL OF THEM, allowing you to set their parameters easily and quickly.
I hope you find it useful!

This version replaces the MusicIN GUI I made in the past.

              @{" REQUIREMENTS " link Requirements} What it needs to work
              @{" INSTALLATION " link Installation} Where to put it
              @{" USAGE        " link Usage} How to use it
              @{" PREFERENCES  " link Prefs} Encoder settings
              @{" HISTORY      " link History} The previous versions
              @{" AUTHOR       " link Author} How to contact me
              @{" BUGS         " link Bugs} Does it work well?

@ENDNODE
@NODE "Requirements" "What it needs to work"

@{JCENTER}@{B}REQUIREMENTS@{UB}

@{JLEFT}The GUI needs:

        - MUI version 3.0 or newer
        - Kickstart 3.0 (V39) or newer.

At least one of the following MPEG audio encoders:

        - 8Hz
        - MusicIN
        - Pegase
        - NCode
        - Lame

        - MPEGA in C: if you want to decode (convert) MPEG to AIFF.

MPEG encoding is a very time consuming task, and requires (not necessarily but recommended) a fast CPU.

@ENDNODE
@NODE "Installation" "Where to put it"

@{JCENTER}@{B}INSTALLATION@{UB}

@{JLEFT}Just copy the program wherever you want. The Tooltypes allow you to specify the locations for the encoders you will use.

@ENDNODE
@NODE "Usage" "How to use it"

@{JCENTER}@{B}USAGE@{UB}

@{JLEFT}Using the GUI is really simple!

In the main window, on the left you can select the source files to be encoded (formats supported: Aiff, Wav or Cdda).
On the right, there is a listing of all the available devices where you may save the MPEG audio file.
After choosing the file to encode and the path for storing the MPEG file, simply start the encoder.

@ENDNODE
@NODE "Prefs" "Encoder settings"

@{JCENTER}@{B}PREFERENCES@{UB}

@{JLEFT}By clicking on the "Preferences" button, at the bottom of the main window, you will open a configuration window, where you can specify the settings for the various encoders with the following gadgets:

@{I}1) Encoder program@{UI}

You may select your preferred encoder: 8Hz, MusicIN, Pegase, NCode or Lame.
(If you are using another encoder, please feel free to contact me, and I will try to support it).

@{I}2) Encoder EXE@{UI}

You have to specify the path for the chosen encoder (the path will be loaded from ToolTypes at every program startup).

Besides selecting the encoder, you may set all the relevant parameters for encoding: their meanings are obvious anyway and every choice can be explained by reading the documentation for the encoder at issue.

@ENDNODE
@NODE "History" "The (many) previous versions"

@{JCENTER}@{B}HISTORY@{UB}

@{JLEFT}@{I}V.1.1a@{UI}

- Support for all most used Amiga encoders: 8Hz, MusicIN, Pegase, NCode and Lame.

@{I}V.1.1@{UI}

- Support also for Pegase encoder
- Localization: the MiraMP3GUI.ct file allows you to quickly create the catalog for your language!
- Added a section for decoding: MPEGA has to be present in your C: directory.

@{I}V1.0a@{UI}

- Added a multiselection requester
- Added the save path.

@{I}V1.0@{UI}

- First version of the GUI.

@ENDNODE
